T • per obedientiam, &c. Thou canſt not be deceiued by thy obedience toward thy Prelate, whom the Church doth beare, Cuſa. lib. 6▪ Exc • t • t▪
yea, though he command other things, then he ought to doe;
vnreaſonable obedience, is the moſt ſound and perfect obedience, that is, when you obey without asking a reaſon thereof, as a beaſt obeyeth his maſter.

